12/02/2007
BANJA LUKA, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- The Principal Deputy High Representative (PDHR) to BiH, Raffi Gregorian, has begun consulting with BiH leaders on police reforms.
In an interview in Monday's (February 12th) edition of Nezavisne novine, he announced that the deadline for achieving a political accord on the issue expires on March 2nd.
Gregorian also reiterated that the chances of BiH sealing a Stabilisation and Association Agreement soon with the EU depends on implementing such key reforms.
He expressed confidence that local leaders, including those from Republika Srpska, are aware of the deadline and predicted an accord on police sector restructuring would be reached.
(Nezavisne novine - 12/02/07)
